	<TEXT>
		<Tag>TXT_KEY_BUILDING_FUNERARY_SERVICES</Tag>
		<English>Funerary Services</English>
	</TEXT>
	<TEXT>
		<Tag>TXT_KEY_BUILDING_FUNERARY_SERVICES_STRATEGY</Tag>
		<English>Allow the building of modern buildings associated with death eg City Morgue. Consolidate you buildings dealing with burial traditions into one building.</English>
	</TEXT>
	<TEXT>
		<Tag>TXT_KEY_BUILDING_FUNERARY_SERVICES_PEDIA</Tag>
		<English>Funerary Services are a game device to consolidate the buildings available in game and control access to future buildings.[PARAGRAPH:2]It represents all the buildings required for the different ways of handling the dead. It is not as good as any of the previous traditions and their buildings but is necessary to build later buildings.</English>
	</TEXT>
	<TEXT>
		<Tag>TXT_KEY_BUILDING_BURIAL_PLATFORMS</Tag>
		<English>Burial Platforms</English>
	</TEXT>
	<TEXT>
		<Tag>TXT_KEY_BUILDING_BURIAL_PLATFORMS_STRATEGY</Tag>
		<English>Improve the ealth of your city by limiting where sky burials happen.</English>
	</TEXT>
	<TEXT>
		<Tag>TXT_KEY_BUILDING_BURIAL_PLATFORMS_PEDIA</Tag>
		<English>While I could find many pictorial examples of this from the Americas, Tibet and Australia I could not find text describing them in general.</English>
	</TEXT>
	<TEXT>
		<Tag>TXT_KEY_BUILDING_BURIAL_TRADITION_STRATEGY</Tag>
		<English>Have different Burial Traditions in different cities to maximise your use of the dead.</English>
	</TEXT>
	<TEXT>
		<Tag>TXT_KEY_BUILDING_BURIAL_TRADITION_CAVE</Tag>
		<English>Burial Tradition (Cave)</English>
	</TEXT>
	<TEXT>
		<Tag>TXT_KEY_BUILDING_BURIAL_TRADITION_CAVE_PEDIA</Tag>
